creator: Hans Christian Andersen
description:
LibriVox recording of Hans Christian Andersen: Fairytales and Short Stories Volume 5, 1860 to 1865 by Hans Christian Andersen. (Translated by H. P. Paull.)
Read in English by NourhanElsayed; Shakira Searle; allenputzig; HariRK; Kristin Gjerløw; Assaf Koss; Jennifer Dorr; John Van Stan; Faith Pak; Jessica Marie; CJ Plog; Muriel; Fred Sandal; Emily Feuka; thestorygirl; Little Tee; nomorejeffs; Jessie Irene
A collection of some of Hans Christian Andersen's works. He is a Danish author and poet most famous for his fairy tales. - Summary by Kristingj
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
subject: librivox; audiobooks;fiction; fairy tales; short works
